\section{Conclusion}
%% ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

An analytical model of a single-phase variable reluctance machine was
developed assuming infinite core permeability.
The self-inductance varies sinusoidally between
$L_{\min} = 8.48\unit{mH}$ (unaligned) and
$L_{\max} = 42.41\unit{mH}$ (aligned).
Under constant DC excitation the torque oscillates at twice the
mechanical frequency with a peak of $106\unit{mN \cdot m}$ and zero mean.
Continuous unidirectional rotation is achieved by energising the coil
only during the unaligned-to-aligned transition, yielding an average
torque of approximately $33.8\unit{mN \cdot m}$.

